PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1780484573
OL,3,CForeign Secretary says Mandelson
OL,4,Cshould 'never have been appointed'
OL,6,FThe second tranche of documents
OL,7,Frevealed Lord Mandelson was highly
OL,8,Fcritical of Starmer's government in
OL,9,Fmessages, saying the prime minister
OL,10,F"lacks verve" and that Chancellor
OL,11,FRachel Reeves could not explain where
OL,12,Feconomic growth would come from.
OL,14,FCooper said that while the release of
OL,15,Fthe files was "unedifying", it was
OL,16,F"right to be transparent" but declined
OL,17,Fto say whether she recognised Lord
OL,18,FMandelson's criticism of the prime
OL,19,Fminister.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1780484573
OL,3,CForeign Secretary says Mandelson
OL,4,Cshould 'never have been appointed'
OL,6,FAsked whether she recognised the
OL,7,Fdisgraced peer's description of
OL,8,FStarmer's approach as "advance,
OL,9,Fbuckle, advance, buckle", the Foreign
OL,10,FSecretary told reporters in Beijing:
OL,11,F"What I would say is that Peter
OL,12,FMandelson should never have been
OL,13,Fappointed as ambassador to the United
OL,14,FStates and, look, of course there's
OL,15,Fbeen a lot of transparency now about
OL,16,Fmessages being released."
OL,18,FCooper declined to answer questions
OL,19,Fabout whether she thought Starmer was
OL,20,Fa "strong and effective leader".
OL,26,@pD@WOUqD@XO]sD@AOU
