PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1780484573
OL,3,CForeign Secretary says Mandelson
OL,4,Cshould 'never have been appointed'
OL,6,FStarmer sacked Lord Mandelson in
OL,7,FSeptember 2025 after leaked emails
OL,8,Fwhich showed the peer sent supportive
OL,9,Fmessages even as Jeffrey Epstein faced
OL,10,Fjail for sex offences.
OL,12,FCabinet minister, Nick Thomas-Symonds,
OL,13,Ftold ITV News that the government were
OL,14,F"determined" to be transparent even if
OL,15,Fit causes embarrassment.
OL,17,FThomas-Symonds could not comply with
OL,18,Fthe request for access as his phone
OL,19,Fwas stolen last year, but he insisted:
OL,20,F"I'm not hiding at all here".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1780484573
OL,3,CForeign Secretary says Mandelson
OL,4,Cshould 'never have been appointed'
OL,6,FHe went on to explain how he exchanged
OL,7,FWhatsApp messages with Mandelson,
OL,8,Fcongratulating each other on their new
OL,9,Froles and discussing the disgraced
OL,10,Fpeer's campaign to become Chancellor
OL,11,Fof the University of Oxford.
OL,13,FWhen questioned about the messages
OL,14,Fshowing a lack of faith in Starmer,
OL,15,FThomas-Symonds defended him, saying
OL,16,Fthat some of those criticisms came at
OL,17,Fa time when the prime minister was
OL,18,Flooking at ways to improve and
OL,19,Frestructure Downing Street, including
OL,20,Fappointing Darren Jones as his Chief
OL,21,FSecretary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1780484573
OL,3,CForeign Secretary says Mandelson
OL,4,Cshould 'never have been appointed'
OL,6,FIn response, the Conservatives' Alex
OL,7,FBurghart said the files reflect
OL,8,F"extremely badly" on the PM's
OL,9,Fjudgement and undermined his
OL,10,F"credibility".
OL,12,FHe expressed his concerns about why
OL,13,Fthe interactions between Starmer and
OL,14,FMandelson appear to be "almost nil"
OL,15,Fand insisted they must have been in
OL,16,Fregular contact.
OL,18,FMPs will have the opportunity to
OL,19,Fdebate the second tranche of files on
OL,20,FWednesday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
